              As a small entrepreneur in accordance with national law, we do not charge VAT, and this tax is not disclosed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="privacy" class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t-2 border-gray-300">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-8 font-headline">Privacy Policy</h1>
        
        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">Last updated: January 2025</p>
            
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              As the operator of this website, Björn Gaworski-Dammann (hereinafter "I" or "We"), take the protection of your personal data very seriously. This policy is designed to be transparent and compliant with the European Union's General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the German Telemedia Act (TMG)/Digital Services Act (DDG).
            </p>

            <div class="pt-6">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Responsible Body (Controller)</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">The responsible body for data processing on this website is:</p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                <p><strong>Björn Gaworski-Dammann</strong></p>
                <p>
                  Schimmelmannstraße 5<br>
                  22043 Hamburg<br>
                  Germany
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@gaworski.de" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">info@gaworski.de</a>
                </p>
                <p>
                  <strong>Telephone:</strong> <a href="tel:+491732585212" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">+49 173 25 85 212</a>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Scope and Purpose of Data Processing</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
                This website is designed to be fully GDPR-compliant. We collect minimal data necessary for website functionality and analytics, only with your explicit consent.
              </p>

              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2.1. Cookie Usage and Consent Management</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    This website uses cookies to ensure proper functionality and to analyze website traffic. We use a cookie consent management system that allows you to control which cookies are set.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Cookie Consent Banner:</strong> When you first visit this website, a cookie consent banner will appear. You can choose to accept all cookies, reject all cookies (except necessary ones), or manage your preferences individually.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Cookie Categories:</strong>
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li><strong>Necessary Cookies:</strong> These cookies are essential for the website to function properly. They cannot be disabled and are always active. These cookies do not collect personal data.</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. These cookies are only set if you give your explicit consent. You can withdraw your consent at any time through the cookie preferences settings.</li>
                    <li><strong>Functionality Cookies:</strong> These cookies enable enhanced functionality and personalization, such as the calendar booking service (Cal.com). These cookies are only set if you give your explicit consent. You can withdraw your consent at any time through the cookie preferences settings.</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                    <strong>Managing Cookie Preferences:</strong> You can change your cookie preferences at any time by clicking on the cookie consent banner or by accessing the cookie preferences through the privacy policy link in the footer.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                    <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. a GDPR (consent) for analytics and functionality cookies. Necessary cookies are based on Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in website functionality).
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2.2. Google Analytics</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    This website uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Ireland Limited ("Google"), Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland. Google Analytics uses cookies to help analyze how users use the site.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Data Collected:</strong> Google Analytics collects information such as:
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li>Page views and navigation paths</li>
                    <li>Time spent on pages</li>
                    <li>Device and browser information</li>
                    <li>Approximate geographic location (country/city level, based on IP address)</li>
                    <li>Referrer information (how you arrived at the website)</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3 mb-3">
                    <strong>IP Anonymization:</strong> We have enabled IP anonymization in Google Analytics. This means your IP address will be truncated by Google within member states of the European Union or other parties to the Agreement on the European Economic Area before transmission to Google servers in the United States. Only in exceptional cases will the full IP address be sent to a Google server in the USA and shortened there.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Data Processing:</strong> The information generated by the cookie about your use of this website is usually transmitted to and stored by Google on servers in the United States. Google may also transfer this information to third parties where required to do so by law, or where such third parties process the information on Google's behalf.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Purpose:</strong> We use Google Analytics to analyze website usage and improve our website's content and user experience. This helps us understand which pages are most popular and how users navigate through the site.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. a GDPR (consent). Google Analytics is only activated after you have given your explicit consent through the cookie consent banner.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>Retention:</strong> Google Analytics data is retained according to Google's data retention settings. You can find more information in Google's Privacy Policy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    <strong>Opt-Out:</strong> You can prevent Google Analytics from collecting data by:
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4 mt-2">
                    <li>Rejecting analytics cookies in the cookie consent banner</li>
                    <li>Installing the Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on: <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout</a></li>
                    <li>Changing your cookie preferences at any time through the cookie consent banner</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2.3. Processing of Data through Direct Communication</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    If you choose to contact me via the provided email address (<a href="mailto:info@gaworski.de" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">info@gaworski.de</a>) or telephone number (<a href="tel:+491732585212" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">+49 173 25 85 212</a>), any personal data transmitted (such as your name, email address, phone number, and the content of your message) will be processed solely for the purpose of handling your inquiry and, if applicable, initiating a contract.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. b GDPR (for contract initiation) or Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in responding to your communication).
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    <strong>Retention:</strong> Data will be retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose of the communication or to comply with legal retention periods (e.g., commercial or tax law).
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2.4. Cal.com Booking Service</h3>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    This website uses Cal.com, a calendar booking service provided by Cal.com, Inc., to enable visitors to schedule appointments directly on the website. Cal.com is an online scheduling platform that allows users to book meetings and appointments.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Data Collected:</strong> When you use the Cal.com booking service, the following data may be collected and processed:
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li>Name</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>Phone number (if provided)</li>
                    <li>Time zone information</li>
                    <li>Selected appointment date and time</li>
                    <li>Additional notes or messages you provide during booking</li>
                    <li>IP address and browser information (for technical functionality)</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3 mb-3">
                    <strong>Data Processing:</strong> Your booking data is processed by Cal.com, Inc. on their servers. Cal.com acts as a data processor on our behalf. The data is used to:
                  </p>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li>Create and manage your appointment booking</li>
                    <li>Send you booking confirmation emails and reminders</li>
                    <li>Sync the appointment with our calendar system</li>
                    <li>Enable communication regarding the scheduled appointment</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3 mb-3">
                    <strong>Third-Party Service:</strong> Cal.com is operated by Cal.com, Inc., a third-party service provider. When you use the booking service, your data may be transmitted to and stored on Cal.com's servers, which may be located outside the European Economic Area (EEA). Cal.com processes your data in accordance with their own privacy policy.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Cal.com Privacy Policy:</strong> For more information about how Cal.com processes your data, please refer to Cal.com's Privacy Policy: <a href="https://cal.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">https://cal.com/privacy</a>
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. b GDPR (contract initiation - necessary for booking and conducting the appointment) and Art. 6(1) lit. a GDPR (consent - for loading the Cal.com booking widget and processing additional data).
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                    <strong>Retention:</strong> Booking data will be retained for as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose of the booking, including conducting the scheduled appointment and any follow-up communications. Data may also be retained for legal compliance purposes (e.g., commercial or tax law requirements). Cal.com may retain data according to their own retention policies as outlined in their privacy policy.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
                    <strong>Your Rights:</strong> You have the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict processing, or object to the processing of your booking data. You also have the right to data portability. To exercise these rights regarding booking data processed through Cal.com, you may contact us at <a href="mailto:info@gaworski.de" class="text-primary hover:text-primary-focus transition duration-150">info@gaworski.de</a> or contact Cal.com directly as outlined in their privacy policy.
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-gray-700">
                    <strong>Consent:</strong> The Cal.com booking widget is only loaded and functional if you have given your consent to functionality cookies through our cookie consent banner. You can withdraw your consent at any time by adjusting your cookie preferences, which will prevent the Cal.com service from loading on future visits.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. Server Log Files (Data Collected by the Hosting Provider)</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                The provider of the pages (web hoster) automatically collects and stores information in so-called server log files, which your browser automatically transmits to us. These include:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li>Browser type and browser version</li>
                <li>Operating system used</li>
                <li>Referrer URL</li>
                <li>Hostname of the accessing computer</li>
                <li>Time of the server request</li>
                <li>IP address</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                This data is not merged with other data sources. The collection of this data is necessary to enable the technical operation of the website and to ensure system security.
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-3">
                <strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR (Legitimate interest in the technical provision and security of the website).
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Your Rights as a Data Subject (GDPR Rights)</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
                Under the GDPR, you have the right to:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li><strong>Right of Access (Art. 15 GDPR):</strong> Request confirmation as to whether personal data concerning you is being processed, and access to that data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Rectification (Art. 16 GDPR):</strong> Request the correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Erasure ('Right to be Forgotten') (Art. 17 GDPR):</strong> Request the deletion of your personal data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Restriction of Processing (Art. 18 GDPR):</strong> Request the restriction of the processing of your personal data.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Data Portability (Art. 20 GDPR):</strong> Receive the personal data concerning you in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Object (Art. 21 GDPR):</strong> Object to the processing of your personal data, particularly if the processing is based on legitimate interests (Art. 6(1) lit. f GDPR).</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
                If you believe that the processing of your personal data violates data protection law, you have the <strong>Right to Lodge a Complaint with a competent supervisory authority</strong> (Art. 77 GDPR). The supervisory authority responsible for me is:
              </p>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mt-2">
                Hamburg Commissioner for Data Protection and Freedom of Information<br>
                Klosterwall 6 (Block C)<br>
                20095 Hamburg<br>
                Germany<br>
                Phone: +49 40 428 54 4040<br>
                Email: mailbox@datenschutz.hamburg.de
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
              <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
              <p class="text-gray-700">
                We reserve the right to amend this data protection declaration at any time in compliance with legal requirements.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

